title: Travis Scott drops Highest in the Room video after Kylie Jenner confirms break-up
text:
Travis Scott has released a music video for his song “Highest in the Room” after Kylie Jenner confirmed their split.

The rapper, 28, first teased the single when Jenner, 22, used it to promote her new line of eyebrow products, called Kybrows.

Now just one day after Jenner confirmed their break-up, Scott has released a surreal music video for his single.

The video sees him smoking, being interrogated by masked men in suits, waking up in a club filled with women pole dancing, being tattooed and fighting with an android while sparks pour out of his eyes.

Surreal: Travis' new video (Dave Meyers/Travis Scott) More

While the song was written prior to the couple’s split, some lyrics seem to suggest the song is about his relationship with the beauty mogul.

In the first verse, he sings: “She saw my eyes, she know I'm gone. I see some things that you might fear. I'm doing a show, I be back soon, that ain't what she wanna hear (No).”

Wanted: He is seen being grabbed by several women in the video (Dave Meyers/Travis Scott) More

It comes after Jenner denied claims she was on a 2am date with her ex Tyga after rumours of the split began to surface.

Photos obtained by MailOnline showed the reality star and her friends Anastasia ‘Stassi’ Karanikolaou and Kelsey Calemine arriving at the Sunset Marquis Hotel in Los Angeles, where the rapper, 29, is thought to have been recording.

Sparks fly: He later receives a tattoo from another woman (Dave Meyers/Travis Scott) More

In a Twitter post shared yesterday, Jenner wrote: “The internet makes everything 100 times more dramatic than what it really is. There was no ‘2am date with Tyga.’ You see me drop two of my friends off at a studio that he happened to be at."
